comment_data.body:
1. Cython isn't an encryption tool and has no interest in being an encryption tool.
2. You just need to put a `u` before the string starting ` "border-right: 1px solid rgb(0, 118, 177);\n"`
3. This probably is a minor Python incompatibility. I don't think it's high priority to fix though
This is the code generated by qt library PySide 6. Can you support this transformation of pyd without manual processing

The directive `language_level=3` fixes it. You can override the default directives in your setup file. This'll also work by default in Cython 3.1 where `language_level=3` is the default option.

Compiling auto-generated PySide code is unlike to be worthwhile though.

milestone.description: Remove support for Python 2 and Python < 3.8.
